article.description: Plomb, Cox lift Army over American U, 68-66
article.headline: Plomb, Cox lift Army over American U, 68-66
article.linkText: Plomb, Cox lift Army over American U, 68-66
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Tanner Plomb made 6 of 9 3-pointers and scored 26, and Dylan Cox hit the go-ahead jumper with four seconds left to help Army slip past American University 68-66 on Monday night. A layup by Marko Vasic gave American (11-9, 4-4 Patriot League) a 66-61 lead with 1:45 remaining. Cox made a layup and, after a back-court violation by American, Plomb knocked down a 3 to tie it with 1:14 to go. Vasic missed a layup on the other end and Plomb grabbed the rebound, setting up Cox's game-winner. Charlie Jones missed a potential winning 3 as time expired. Kyle Wilson scored 16 and Kevin Ferguson added 14 for Army (13-6, 4-4), which improved to 5-0 in game decided by three points or less. John Schoof led the Eagles with 17 points, Jones added 12 and Jesse Reed had 10 to go with eight rebounds.
